JAPAN DAYBOOK: Tepco Sees Reactor Shutdown in Six Months

-- B y   S t e v e n   M c P h e r s o n
-- 
2011-04-17T20:58:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/japan-daybook-tepco-sees-reactor-shutdown-in-six-months.html
Tokyo Electric Power said it
expects to achieve a cold shutdown at its nuclear plants within
six months. The utility will sell shares of phone operator KDDI
to raise funds to compensate of victims of its nuclear crisis,
the Nikkei newspaper reported.  WHAT TO WATCH
*Tokyo Electric Power plans to end the crisis at its tsunami-
 hit nuclear plant within six months
*Tokyo Electric Power plans to sell KDDI shares to make
 nuclear compensation payments, the Nikkei newspaper reported
*Toyota plans engine plant in devastated  Miyagi prefecture ,
 Managing Director Sakurai says in interview
*Nissan plans to sell about 30 billion yen of bonds this week,
 according to a person with direct knowledge of the deal
*Nissan will recall 5,300 LEAF electric cars after “a very
 small proportion” failed to restart once turned off  GOVERNMENT
